<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id911a61a1-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s8930"><num value="8930">§ 8930.</num><heading> Rule of construction</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Nothing in this chapter shall be construed as an authorization for the use of military force.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id911a61a2-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">(<ref href="/us/pl/113/272/s11">Pub. L. 113–272, § 11</ref>, <date date="2014-12-18">Dec. 18, 2014</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/128/2966">128 Stat. 2966</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id911a61a3-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id911a61a4-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I75" topic="referencesInText" id="id911a61a5-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">References in Text</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">This chapter, referred to in text, was in the original “this Act or an amendment made by this Act”, meaning <ref href="/us/pl/113/272">Pub. L. 113–272</ref>, <date date="2014-12-18">Dec. 18, 2014</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/128/2952">128 Stat. 2952</ref>, which enacted this chapter and provisions set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t22/s8921">section 8921 of this title</ref>. <ref href="/us/pl/113/272">Pub. L. 113–272</ref> did not make any amendments.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
